.TH "vc4_create_object" 9 "vc4_create_object" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vc4_create_object \- Implementation of driver->gem_create_object.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct drm_gem_object *" vc4_create_object
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "size" 12
Size in bytes of the memory the object will reference
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This lets the CMA helpers allocate object structs for us, and keep
our BO stats correct.
